subSubSection.paragraph:
Female terminalia
(
Figs 15–20
). Tergite 10 shiny brown. Cercus brownish yellow, about as long as tergite 10, slender with up-turned tip (
Fig. 15
). Ventral margin distally with small, distinct serrations. Hypovalva pale, elongated, filamentous, with short trichia at tip (
Fig. 15
). Median incision between hypovalvae deeper than posterior margin of sternite 8. Lateral incision deep and narrow, about three times as deep as maximum width. Posterolateral angle of sternite 8 rounded. Sternite 9 with posterior part shovel-shaped, margin with lateral incisions, medially forming groove; anterior parts flattened (
Fig. 17
). Furca flattened, base narrow (
Fig. 18
). Bursa copulatrix with spermathecal ducts sclerotised at the base, in shape of curved, slender, dark brown sticks (
Fig. 19
). Cul-de-sac of bursa copulatrix curved. Spermatheca pear-shaped (
Fig. 20
).
